<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>Alternatives to storing visuals\u00a0on your website<\/h2>\n<p>As you can see, there is no excuse\u00a0not to\u00a0use\u00a0impressive visuals in your\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2016\/06\/30\/social-media-advertising-tips\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">social media content<\/a>\u00a0marketing,\u00a0given the multitude of available tools! However, it is crucial to remember the speed\u00a0at\u00a0which audiences consume your information on your website or landing pages, and that\u00a0eye-catching\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/bluetree.ai\/website-design-tips\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">visuals can hinder the user experience<\/a>\u00a0by slowing down\u00a0load\u00a0times. If images and other visuals take too long to load, your site visitors will get frustrated and leave.<\/p>\n<p>However, the solution is simple. Be sure to optimize\u00a0and compress your self-hosted\u00a0visuals with free tools such as JPEG Optimizer, Compress Now, and Tiny PNG.<\/p>\n<p>Although optimizing and compressing visual content on your website and landing pages will improve site speed, you may also want to\u00a0consider\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cloudwards.net\/best-online-storage-for-photos\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">using\u00a0online storage to free up space<\/a>\u00a0on your mobile devices or website\u00a0hosting platform.<\/p>\n<p>Online storage is also a protective measure should your site experience malicious attacks that compromise or corrupt your data, information, and visual content.<\/p>\n<h2>The future of visual marketing<\/h2>\n<p>There is no\u00a0question\u00a0that\u00a0marketing trends\u00a0will continue to shift over time as technology advances and\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2019\/11\/21\/customer-journey-mapping\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">consumer preferences<\/a>\u00a0change.\u00a0\u00a0What will remain the same is the usage of\u00a0visual content\u00a0as an integral way for brands to connect with their audiences.\u00a0Be sure to align your marketing campaigns with your brand. Continue to create relevant, eye-catching, and appealing visuals to attract your target market to your messages.<\/p>\n<h3>About the author<\/h3>\n<p>Julie Weishaar is the Visual Digital Marketing Specialist who founded <a href=\"https:\/\/newhorizons123.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">New Horizons 123<\/a>. She works to help small businesses increase their online visibility and grow by leveraging the latest in internet and video technologies. Julie specializes in creative camera-less animated video production, custom images, content writing, and SlideShare presentations. She also manages HubSpot CRM, blog management, email marketing, marketing automation, and social media for her clients.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how to create relevant, eye-catching, and appealing visuals to attract your target market to your branding and messages using five favorite platforms: Bannersnack, Venngage, Canva, Venngage, and Lumen5.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":164,"featured_media":320,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"_et_pb_use_builder":"","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[12],"tags":[],"dipi_cpt_category":[],"class_list":["post-10248","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-content-marketing"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v25.8 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>5 Powerful Visual Marketing Tools To Enchant Your Audience and Boost ROI<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Learn how to create relevant, eye-catching, and appealing visuals to attract your target market to your branding and messages using five favor